<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="60" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="60">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="60">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Mulsant, 1850" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Aspidimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidimerus ruficrus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficrus">Aspidimerus ruficrus</taxonomicName>
in general appearance, but can be distinguished by the stout, strongly curved penis guide in lateral view and symmetrical with obtuse apex in ventral view (Figs 71-72). In 
<taxonomicName authority="Mulsant, 1850" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Aspidimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidimerus ruficrus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficrus">Aspidimerus ruficrus</taxonomicName>
, penis guide slender, slightly straight in lateral view and vase-shaped with truncate apex in ventral view (Figs 81-82). The shape of penis is also diagnostic (Fig. 69).
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="13" pageNumber="60">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="60">
Figures 79-84. 
<taxonomicName authority="Mulsant, 1850" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Aspidimerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidimerus ruficrus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficrus">Aspidimerus ruficrus</taxonomicName>
Gorham, 79-82 male genitalia: 79 penis 80 apex of penis 81 tegmen, ventral view 82 tegmen, lateral view 83-84 female genitalia: 83 spermatheca 84 ovipositor. Scale bars: 0.1mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
